The league has also confirmed that the awards will return to the Sandton Convention Centre on 10 July 2017. CAPE TOWN - The Premier Soccer League (PSL) has announced the full list of nominees for the 2016/17 league awards.The Footballer of the Season category will see the league s top scorer Lebogang Manyama go up against Wits' league-winning captain Thulani Hlatshwayo and Mamelodi Sundowns captain Hlompho Kekana.In the Player s Player of the Year category, Cape Town City s dynamic duo of Manyama and Aubrey Ngoma are joined by the talented Sundowns attacker Percy Tau.While victorious PSL coach Gavin Hunt of Wits will tussle with Eric Tinkler (formerly of Cape Town City) and Pitso Mosimane for the Coach of the Season award.The league has also confirmed that the awards will return to the Sandton Convention Centre on 10 July 2017.Below is the list all of nominees and categories:Footballer of the Season Hlompho Kekana (Mamelodi Sundowns) Thulani Hlatshwayo (Bidvest Wits) Lebogang Manyama (Cape Town City)Absa Premiership Top Goal Scorer Lebogang Manyama (Cape Town City)Absa Premiership Player's Player of the Season Lebogang Manyama (Cape Town City) Aubrey Ngoma (Cape Town City) Percy Tau (Mamelodi Sundowns)Absa Premiership Goalkeeper of the Season Darren Keet (Bidvest Wits) Dennis Onyango (Mamelodi Sundowns) Shu-Aib Walters (Cape Town City)Absa Premiership Defender of the Season Thulani Hlatshwayo (Bidvest Wits) Sifiso Hlanti (Bidvest Wits) Ramahlwe Mphahlele (Kaizer Chiefs)Absa Premiership Midfielder of the Season Hlompho Kekana (Mamelodi Sundowns) Thabang Monare (Bidvest Wits) Aubrey Ngoma (Cape Town City)Absa Premiership Young Player of the Season Motjeka Madisha (Mamelodi Sundowns) Phakamani Mahlambi (Bidvest Wits) Nduduzo Sibiya (L. Golden Arrows)Absa Premiership Coach of the Season Gavin Hunt (Bidvest Wits) Pitso Mosimane (Mamelodi Sundowns) Eric Tinkler (Cape Town City)NFD Goal Scorer Sedwyn George (Royal Eagles)Telkom Knockout Player of the Tournament Michael Boxall (SuperSport United) Lebogang Manyama (Cape Town City) Aubrey Ngoma (Cape Town City)Nedbank Cup Young Player of Tournament Siyabonga Dube (L. Golden Arrows) Nduduzo Sibiya (L. Golden Arrows) Teboho Mokoena (SuperSport United)Nedbank Cup Player of the Tournament Mpho Makola (Orlando Pirates) Teboho Mokoena (SuperSport United) Abbubaker Mobara (Orlando Pirates)MTN8 Last Man Standing Daine Klate (Bidvest Wits) Thulani Hlatshwayo (Bidvest Wits) Gabadinho Mhango (Bidvest Wits)Referee of the Season Christopher Harrison Phelelani Ndaba Thando NdzandzekaAssistant Referee Xolani Duma Luvuyo Pupuma Mervyn van WykMULTICHOICE DISKI CHALLENGE Keletso Makgalwa (Mamelodi Sundowns) Motjeka Madisha (Mamelodi Sundowns) Mlondi Dlamini (Maritzburg United)